In this document we simplify the expressions of Schreiber and Fitting
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schreiber2001,Schreiber2002"

\end_inset

.
 For general applications, we assume that detailed information on the band
 structure is not available.
 As a first approximation, we choose the band structure of a free electron.
 In other words, we assume a parabolic band with
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=0$
\end_inset

 and effective density of states mass
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $m_{D}=m_{e}$
\end_inset

.
 In this case, the density of states as a function of energy is given by,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
D\!\left(E\right)=\frac{\sqrt{2m_{e}^{3}E}}{\pi^{2}\hbar^{3}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

Furthermore, we assume that phonon scattering applies to electron energies
 where relativistic corrections can be neglected.
 The energy at the Brilliouin zone boundary equals,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E_{BZ}=\frac{\left(\hbar k_{BZ}\right)^{2}}{2m_{e}}=\frac{h^{2}}{2m_{e}a^{2}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is the lattice constant.
 The total scattering cross-section
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E\right)$
\end_inset

 due to acoustic phonon scattering is calculated as follows,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E\right)=\frac{P_{ac}\!\left(E\right)}{\rho_{n}v\!\left(E\right)}=\sqrt{\frac{m_{e}}{2E}}\frac{P_{ac}\!\left(E\right)}{\rho_{n}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{n}$
\end_inset

 is the number density.
 We have substituted
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $v\!\left(E\right)$
\end_inset

 with the non-relativistic velocity of the electron as a function of energy.
 The screened scattering rate
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $P_{ac}$
\end_inset

 in the low energy limit
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ}$
\end_inset

 is given by Schreiber and Fitting and equals,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ}\right)=\frac{\pi\epsilon_{ac}^{2}k_{B}T}{\hbar c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}}\frac{A}{A+E}D\!\left(E\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{ac}$
\end_inset

 is the acoustic deformation potential,
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $c_{s}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

the sound velocity,
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{m}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

the mass density and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

is the screening factor as introduced by Bradford and Woolf 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Bradford1991"

\end_inset

.
 The total scattering cross-section in the low energy limit is evaluated
 as,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ}\right)=\frac{m_{e}^{2}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}k_{B}T}{\pi\hbar^{4}c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}\frac{A}{A+E}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

The screened scattering rate
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $P_{ac}$
\end_inset

 in the high energy limit
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $E>E_{BZ}$
\end_inset

 is also given by Schreiber and Fitting and equals,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ}\right)=\frac{4\pi\left(2n_{BZ}+1\right)m_{e}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}}{\hbar^{2}\omega_{BZ}\rho_{m}}\frac{A^{2}}{E}\left(\ln\frac{A+E}{A}-\frac{E}{A+E}\right)D\!\left(E\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $n_{BZ}$
\end_inset

 is the acoustic phonon density (population).
 Note that, contrary to Ref.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schreiber2001"

\end_inset

, a factor of
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\hbar$
\end_inset

 is missing in the denominator of Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

12b in Ref.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schreiber2002"

\end_inset

.
 The total scattering cross-section in the high energy limit is evaluated
 as,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ}\right)=\frac{2\left(2n_{BZ}+1\right)m_{e}^{3}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}a}{\pi\text{Â²}\hbar^{5}c_{s}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}\frac{A^{2}}{E}\left(\ln\frac{A+E}{A}-\frac{E}{A+E}\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

where we have used
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{BZ}=k_{BZ}c_{s}=\frac{2\pi c_{s}}{a}$
\end_inset

.
 The acoustic phonon density
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $n_{BZ}$
\end_inset

 is given by Ref.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Zhao2004"

\end_inset

 and equals,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
n_{BZ}=\frac{1}{\exp\frac{\hbar\omega_{BZ}}{k_{B}T}-1}=\frac{k_{B}T}{\hbar\omega_{BZ}}-\frac{1}{2}+\mathcal{O}\left(\hbar\omega_{BZ}\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

We now substitute the expansion of the acoustic phonon density into the
 high energy limit of the total scattering cross-section.
 The result is,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ}\right) & = & \frac{2m_{e}^{3}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}a^{2}k_{B}T}{\pi^{3}\hbar^{6}c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}\frac{A^{2}}{E}\left(\ln\frac{A+E}{A}-\frac{E}{A+E}\right)
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

We would like to point out that in the simulator of Ref.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Kieft2008"

\end_inset

, a factor of 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 is missing in the denominator.
 The differential scattering cross-section is obtained by normalizing the
 angular distributions from Ref.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schreiber2002"

\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{\textrm{d}\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ},\theta\right)}{\textrm{d}\Omega} & = & \frac{\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ}\right)}{2\pi}\frac{\frac{1}{2}\left(1+\frac{E}{A}\right)}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}\nonumber \\
 & = & \frac{1}{4}\frac{m_{e}^{2}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}k_{B}T}{\pi^{2}\hbar^{4}c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}\frac{1}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{\textrm{d}\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ},\theta\right)}{\textrm{d}\Omega} & = & \frac{\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ}\right)}{2\pi}\frac{\frac{1}{2}\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E^{2}}{A^{2}}}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}\left(\ln\frac{A+E}{A}-\frac{E}{A+E}\right)}\nonumber \\
 & = & \frac{1}{2}\frac{m_{e}^{3}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}a^{2}k_{B}T}{\pi^{4}\hbar^{6}c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}\frac{\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}E}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

In summary, we define the following constant,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sigma_{ac}=\frac{m_{e}^{2}\epsilon_{ac}^{2}k_{B}T}{\pi\hbar^{4}c_{s}^{2}\rho_{m}\rho_{n}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

which is the total acoustic phonon scattering cross-section evaluated at
 
\begin_inset Formula $E=0$
\end_inset

.
 The angular differential scattering cross-sections are then expressed as,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\textrm{d}\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ},\theta\right)}{\textrm{d}\Omega}=\frac{\sigma_{ac}}{4\pi}\frac{1}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\textrm{d}\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ},\theta\right)}{\textrm{d}\Omega}=\frac{\sigma_{ac}}{4\pi}\frac{4A}{E_{BZ}}\frac{\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
noindent 
\end_layout

\end_inset

The total scattering cross-sections are obtained by integrating the respective
 angular differential cross-sections,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E<\frac{1}{4}E_{BZ}\right) & = & \frac{\sigma_{ac}}{4\pi}\int_{0}^{2\pi}\!\textrm{d}\varphi\int_{0}^{\pi}\!\frac{\sin\theta\textrm{d}\theta}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}\nonumber \\
 & = & \frac{A}{A+E}\sigma_{ac}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\sigma_{ac}\!\left(E>E_{BZ}\right) & = & \frac{\sigma_{ac}}{4\pi}\frac{4A}{E_{BZ}}\int_{0}^{2\pi}\!\textrm{d}\varphi\int_{0}^{\pi}\!\frac{\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}}{\left(1+\frac{1-\cos\theta}{2}\frac{E}{A}\right)^{2}}\sin\theta\textrm{d}\theta\nonumber \\
 & = & \frac{4A}{E_{BZ}}\left(\frac{A+E}{E}\ln\frac{A+E}{A}-1\right)\frac{A}{A+E}\sigma_{ac}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\end_layout

